				\begin{document}$$w_{j} = (1 - w_{i} ) \times \frac{{w_{j0} }}{{(1 - w_{i0} )}}$$\end{document}where wi0 is the weight of the main affecting criterion. wi and wj is the new weight value assigned to the ith and jth criterion. wi0 and wj0 are the weights of criterion i and j, which are used as an input at base run.
